The Vice President released a statement emphasizing the importance of passing the New START Treaty for national security. He highlighted the benefits of ratifying the treaty, including the ability to inspect Russia's nuclear activities, track their nuclear arsenal, and promote cooperation between the two countries. The Vice President also mentioned the treaty's role in supporting troops in Afghanistan and imposing sanctions on Iran. He noted that the treaty has broad bipartisan support, with endorsements from former officials from both parties. The Vice President emphasized the need for prompt action to approve the treaty before the end of the year.